Following a report, a Non-Governmental Organization, Sahel Initiative for Justice on Sunday visited the Jajere community in Fune Local Government Area of Yobe State to support a vulnerable woman. Raihanatu who was reported by the Jajere Emirate Council as a destitute sleeping in the market square with her 7 months baby.Sahel Initiative for Justice to women and Children quickly intervened immediately by visiting Jajere town today, as a result, her parents were traced to be residing in a nearby village. The Executive Director Sahel Initiative for Justice Barrister Altine Ibrahim told Daily Independent that services rendered to the vulnerable include psychosocial support “and she seems to be stabilized” . “The parents also were educated on the effects of trauma and how to control its recurrence. “She was successfully reunited with her parents and was also supported with some hygiene and non-food items by the organization, which includes Blanket, mosquito net, mat, Bar soap, detergent, pants, sanitary towels, Vaseline, torchlight, bucket among other utensils”. On his part, the district head of Jajere commended the organization for their prompt intervention and prayed for their success in life and also urged people to support and cooperate for further intervention.